<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10145080>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Vectius niger (Simon, 1880). A–C Male. A–B palp: A ventral view. B retrolateral view. C, cheliceral teeth, ventral view, D Female, epigynum, ventral view. Abbreviations: A, atrium; MA, median apophysis; C, cymbium; EB, embolar base; ELF, spigynal lateral field; EMF, epigynal median field; EPP, embolar base proximal projection; MA, median apophysis; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; T, tegulum." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10145080/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10145082>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Vectius niger (Simon, 1880). A–C Male. A Body, dorsal view. B−C palp. B ventral view. C retrolateral view. D–E Female epigynum. D ventral view. E dorsal view. Abbreviations:A, atrium; C, cymbium; CD, copulatory duct; E, embolus; EB, embolar base; ELF, spigynal lateral field; EMF, epigynal median field; EPP, embolar base proximal projection; FD, fertilization duct; MA, median apophysis; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermathecae." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10145082/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10145084>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Geographical distribution of Vectius niger (Simon, 1880) in the Neotropical region. The grey area indicates the country Brazil." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10145084/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

